ivardefs.name: coordinateSystem
ivardefs.desc: Whether the sequence is numbered starting at 0 (0-based numbering or coordinates, inclusive start, exclusive end) or starting at 1 (1-based numbering, inclusive start and inclusive end).

ivardefs.name: device
ivardefs.desc: The method for sequencing, for example, chip information.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: A unique identifier for this particular sequence instance. This is a FHIR-defined id.

ivardefs.name: observedSeq
ivardefs.desc: Sequence that was observed. It is the result marked by referenceSeq along with variant records on referenceSeq. This shall start from referenceSeq.windowStart and end by referenceSeq.windowEnd.

ivardefs.name: patient
ivardefs.desc: The patient whose sequencing results are described by this resource.

ivardefs.name: performer
ivardefs.desc: The organization or lab that should be responsible for this result.

ivardefs.name: pointer_
ivardefs.desc: Pointer to next atomic sequence which at most contains one variant.

ivardefs.name: quality_
ivardefs.desc: An experimental feature attribute that defines the quality of the feature in a quantitative way, such as a phred quality score ([SO:0001686](http://www.sequenceontology.org/browser/current_svn/term/SO:0001686)).

ivardefs.name: quantity
ivardefs.desc: The number of copies of the sequence of interest. (RNASeq).

ivardefs.name: readCoverage
ivardefs.desc: Coverage (read depth or depth) is the average number of reads representing a given nucleotide in the reconstructed sequence.

ivardefs.name: referenceSeq
ivardefs.desc: A sequence that is used as a reference to describe variants that are present in a sequence analyzed.

ivardefs.name: repository_
ivardefs.desc: Configurations of the external repository. The repository shall store target's observedSeq or records related with target's observedSeq.

ivardefs.name: type
ivardefs.desc: Amino Acid Sequence/ DNA Sequence / RNA Sequence.

ivardefs.name: variant_
ivardefs.desc: The definition of variant here originates from Sequence ontology ([variant_of](http://www.sequenceontology.org/browser/current_svn/term/variant_of)). This element can represent amino acid or nucleic sequence change(including insertion,deletion,SNP,etc.)

properties.desc: Raw data describing a biological sequence.
